
How-to:


/******************************************************************************************************
*** 								ECLIPSE															***	
*******************************************************************************************************/
From eclipse:

* Select the project
* Right click on the project 
* Run As -> Gradle build
* Type the following tasks to run:
	clean build 
	bootRun
* bootRun will start the application from the jar, 
	behind the scenes it starts an embedded Apache Tomcat Server



/******************************************************************************************************
*** 							COMMAND LINE														***	
*******************************************************************************************************/

Before trying make sure Gradle is on your path.


From the command line execute:

prompt> cd ${your_git_home}\examples\RestServiceSpringGradle
prompt> gradle clean build && java -jar build/libs/my-rest-service-1.0.jar

For stopping... use the key combination:

prompt> Ctrl + C

